<headline>Freeze Warning issued November 02 at 5:48AM EDT until November 02 at 9:00AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...FREEZE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT THIS MORNING...
* WHAT...Sub-freezing temperatures as low as the upper teens to
mid 20s.
* WHERE...The Virginia and North Carolina foothills and
piedmont, as well as the Roanoke Valley.
* WHEN...This Morning.
* IMPACTS...Frost and freeze conditions will kill remaining crops,
other sensitive vegetation and possibly damage unprotected
outdoor plumbing.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...This mornings hard, killing freeze, will
end the growing season for 2023.</description>
<instruction>As we transition into the late fall and early winter, now is the
time to winterize pipes to prevent freezing and possible bursting,
especially those that are exposed to the outdoors. Outdoor water
pipes should be wrapped, drained, or allowed to drip slowly. Water
hoses should be disconnected from your house and drained. Those
that have in-ground sprinkler systems should drain them and cover
above-ground pipes to protect them from freezing.</instruction>
